OL,6,FThe majority of the new constituency
OL,7,Fnames are in Welsh - which has
OL,8,Freceived mixed reaction.
OL,10,FCampaign group Cymdeithas yr Iaith
OL,11,F(Welsh Language Society) has welcomed
OL,12,Fthe Welsh-only names and encourages
OL,13,Fthe Commission to go a step further.
OL,15,FSian Howys, Vice-Chair of Cymdeithas
OL,16,Fyr Iaith, said: "Welsh is the unique
OL,17,Fnational language of Wales, and we
OL,18,Fshould be proud of it, use it and
OL,19,Fpromote it so that seeing and hearing
OL,20,FWelsh words and placenames becomes
OL,21,Fnormal.
