OL,4,Cdivides opinion
OL,6,F"We will continue to press in our
OL,7,Fresponse to the new proposals for also
OL,8,Fusing the Welsh language for the four
OL,9,Fcurrent exceptions - in Caerdydd and
OL,10,FAbertawe. It would be possible to give
OL,11,Fnames that do not include compass
OL,12,Fdirections, so that they do not need
OL,13,Fto be translated, for example Gwyr-
OL,14,FTawe instead of Swansea West Gower."
OL,16,FBut the move has been blasted as a way
OL,17,Fto "disenfranchise English-only
OL,18,Fspeakers" by former Leader of the
OL,19,FWelsh Conservatives, Andrew RT Davies
OL,20,FMS.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/9
